HEADWORD: Overgloom
<hw>O`ver*gloom"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To spread
gloom over; to make gloomy; to overshadow.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Overgloomed</qex> by memories of sorrow.</q> <rj><qau>De
Quincey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overgo</ent>⟦br⟧
